news.title: Bengaluru metro's airport line 49 properties away
news.para: ​While the BMRCL has been able to acquire 224 properties (175 private and 49 government), it is yet to acquire 49 (38 private and 11 government) properties. Sources said that once these properties are acquired, then the entire project will be fast tracked.

news.title: Kolkata: Get jabbed twice, claim property tax discount
news.para: To encourage people to take both the doses of Covid vaccine, South Dum Dum Municipality is planning to allow a 25% relaxation on unpaid property tax if all the family members of the household furnish their vaccination certificate.

news.title: PVC pipe makers set for 35% revenue growth this fiscal: Crisil
news.para: This fiscal, operating profitability is expected to moderate to 16-17% from the peak of last fiscal, mainly due to higher PVC resin prices, which are being passed on with a lag, and higher freight costs.

news.title: Allotment of plots begins at MIDC's Ajang estate
news.para: This new estate is spread over 345 hectare and the MIDC has allotted plots to over 200 MSMEs in food and textile sectors that are expected to fetch investment amounting to Rs 1,000 crore during the next two-three years and will provide employments to over 4,000 people.

news.title: Sand set to get cheaper in Maharashtra under new mining policy
news.para: In a press release, the government said the new policy will ensure that river and creek sand and gravel is available at a more reasonable rate and the license for sand mining will be valid for five years after the successful auctioneer has obtained a letter of intent along with environmental permits.

news.title: PNB Housing Finance's net profit down 19% at Rs 188 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income during October-December period of 2021-22 stood at Rs 1,495.61 crore, down by 26.8 per cent from Rs 1,896.35 crore in same quarter of 2020-21, PNB Housing Finance said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Why are we charged for infrastructure: Gurugram residents to DHBVN
news.para: However, this decision of Dakshin Haryana Bijli Vitran Nigam (DHBVN) to recover the ‘development charges’ from new consumers or existing ones seeking load enhancement has drawn flak from the residents.

news.title: Unassessed properties under Kolkata civic body scanner
news.para: The move is part of a revenue augmentation drive. KMC assessment department inspectors were asked to prepare a list of unassessed properties and then bring them under the assessment ambit so that the civic body starts receiving property tax from these addresses.

news.title: Over 57,000 buildings illegal in Ludhiana: Report
news.para: ​Citing big difference between new electricity connections issued by PSPCL and new building plans approved by the MC’s building branch, the officer has observed that carelessness of the civic officials is not only encouraging lawlessness in the city, but also proving detrimental to the financial health of the civic body.

news.title: Institutional real estate investment dips 14% at $4.3 billion in 2021: JLL
news.para: Investments in the office sector accounted for the largest share of 31% during 2021 while it was highly skewed during 2020 due to two large portfolio deals amounting to USD 3.2 billion.

news.title: Builders upload progress information after Rajasthan RERA warning
news.para: To provide transparent records to buyers as per the mandatory provision, the promoters must upload the project updates on apartments/flats, status update of each building, floor, internal infrastructure and common area constructions on the RERA website at the end of each quarter.

news.title: Mapletree Logistics buys land on the outskirts of Bengaluru for Rs 110 crore
news.para: Mapletree had in 2021, ventured into the fast-growing logistics space with the purchase of a majority stake in logistics firm KSH Infra from a unit of Morgan Stanley Real Estate Investing (MSREI) for around Rs 455 crore.

news.title: Real estate frauds arrested for cheating investors of Rs 1.75 crore
news.para: Two real estate dealers were arrested for embezzling people's money invested in luxury apartments in Delhi/NCR, police said on Thursday.

news.title: Noida: RWAs want freehold status for property, but without extra fee
news.para: As per the freehold system, an allottee gets outright ownership of the property. The leasehold system gives an allottee the ownership of the property only for 90 years.

news.title: Settlrs raises $1 million from Canbank Ventures, others
news.para: It provides furniture, home appliances, fitness equipment and IT infrastructure to startups and co-living spaces on a lease basis. The company may foray into the B2C space, its founder Gaurav Ranebennur told ET over phone.
